From c3ebee332d33d8ea2aa6895cc803565831d900e5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: alexfrljuckic <alexfrljuckic@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 17:01:40 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] feat: configurable Span HUD for 2.0 (ultrawide HUD to
 screen edges)

Ports master's SpanAllHUD to the 2.0 rewrite. Master's UI-Constraints
pattern still matches uniquely; at +0x1C the element constraint w/h are
freshly loaded (vmovss xmm2,[rax+0x1BC]/xmm0,[rax+0x1C0]). Struct layout
recovered via an in-mod diagnostic hook (anti-debug blocks x64dbg):
ref/constraint dims at 0x1B4/0x1B8 and 0x1BC/0x1C0. Spans any element
authored at 3840x2160 by overriding the register (no struct mutation).
Excludes world-positioned elements (NPC quest bubbles) via the
rax+0x1CC position-offset sentinel so markers stay pinned. New [Span HUD]
config (Enabled + AspectRatio).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
